.TH "base64_encode" 9 "base64_encode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
base64_encode \- base64-encode some bytes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" base64_encode
.BI "(const u8 *src "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "char *dst "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "src" 12
the bytes to encode
.IP "len" 12
number of bytes to encode
.IP "dst" 12
(output) the base64-encoded string.  Not NUL-terminated.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Encodes the input string using characters from the set [A-Za-z0-9+,].
The encoded string is roughly 4/3 times the size of the input string.
.SH "RETURN"
length of the encoded string
